x4freetext: 1. The First Correction Concerned Elastically Scattered
Deutrons Which Emerged at Angle Greater Than 30 Angular
Degrees. This Correction was Negative and Less Than 9%
2.The Second Correction was For Nuclear Reactions
Producing Charged Particles Which Entered Detector with
Energies Above Discriminator Level For the Detector.
This Correction was Positive Ans Always Less Than 3.5%
3. Corection on False Detected Reaction Products.
4. Correction on Undetected Deutrons was Negative and
5. Correction Due to Finitetarget Thickness and Finite
Beam Size were Estimated to be Negligible.
See in Original Paper. Some Plastic Scintillators were
Combined by Coincinence and Anticoincidence Device.
